<HEAD>News Of Arrest Arrives After Victims' Funeral</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Winery Slayings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PETALUMA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Six members of a family killed in a
winery worker's jealous rage were buried, and the service was
followed shortly by word of the alleged killer's arrest in Mexico.
   Some 50 mourners attended the private service Wednesday at
Calvary Catholic Cemetery as dozens of Sonoma County sheriff's
deputies roamed the perimeter with binoculars and radios.
   The tight security stemmed from fear that Ramon Salcido, 28,
might still be in the area. But Salcido was arrested in Mexico
later Wednesday and confessed in a television interview to killing
his wife, two daughters, his mother-in-law, two of her daughters
and one of his co-workers last week.
   Salcido, 28, told police he thought his wife had been having an
affair with the co-worker.
   At the funeral, Robert Richards and his sons, Gerald, Robert Jr.
and Louis, carried six coffins. They contained the bodies of
Richards' wife, Marian Louise, 47; his three daughters, Marie, 8,
Ruth 12, and Angela, 24, who was Salcido's wife; and granddaughters
Sofia, 4, and Teresa, 1.
   ``I don't know how anyone could survive this mentally without a
belief in God,'' said Judith Kelly, a friend of the Salcido family
for 13 years who said she attended church with them. ``There's a
reason for everything, and I know the whole family and all the rest
of us feel that way.
   ``You have to accept this, but this is not going to answer the
question, `Why?''' she said. ``We don't know why.''
   The Rev. Kenneth Cabral, a retired Roman Catholic priest and
longtime friend of the Richards, recited the rosary and officiated.
   White caskets carrying the four dead children and gray caskets
containing the adults were taken one by one from a mausoleum at the
cemetery to the burial site, then lowered into the ground along
with metal crucifixes and flowers.
   Kelly said the three Richards sons attending agreed they want
the surviving Salcido child, Carmina, 3, to live with a family
member when she recovers from injuries suffered when her father
allegedly cut her throat and abandoned her at a dump with her dead
sisters, whose throats were also cut.
