<FIRST>r a PM-MIA-RemainsIdentified 1stLd-Writethru a0506 04-20 0201</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-MIA-Remains Identified, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0506,0198</SECOND>
<HEAD>Military Identifies Six Sets of Remains of Vietnam Era Servicemen</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS last graf to CORRECT spelling of Lynn sted Lynne. Kenedy
is cq in 3rd graf</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONOLULU (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The remains of six Air Force servicemen killed
during the Vietnam War have been identified from among 38 sets of
remains repatriated by Vietnam on Dec. 15, the military said.
   The Army's Central Identification Laboratory announced the
identifications Wednesday. The Defense Department scheduled a full
military honors ceremony today for four of the men before their
remains are sent from Hickam Air Force Base near Honolulu to Travis
Air Force Base, Calif., for return to their families.
   The Defense Department identified the six lost over North
Vietnam as Col. Kenneth D. Robinson of Indianapolis; Maj. Sammie D.
Hoff of Kenedy, Texas; Maj. Robert R. Lynn of Jacksonville, Ill.;
Capt. Richard J. Mallon of Portland, Ore.; Capt. Donovan K. Walters
of Lebanon, Neb.; and Master Sgt. Charles J. Bebus of Osseo, Minn.
   Robinson and Hoff had been listed as missing in action since
Aug. 30, 1966; Lynn, Walters and Bebus since Dec. 21, 1972; and
Mallon since Jan. 28, 1970, military officials said.
</TEXT>
