<HEAD>Hailstorm Kills 45 in Sichuan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hailstorm battered a city in southwest China's
Sichuan province early Thursday, killing 45 people and injuring
119, a news report said.
   The hailstorm struck Luzhou City shortly after midnight, and
lasted about half an hour, the official Xinhua News Agency said.
   The storm cut of water, electricity and telephone services,
uprooted trees and smashed 40 percent of windows and doors in
high-rise buildings.
   Ten percent of single-story homes in the area collapsed. The
report did not give the population of the area.
   Xinhua said the exact casualty and damage figures were not
available because communications links with Luzhou were severed.
   The Sichuan government sent rescue teams to the area, it said.
