<HEAD>U.S.-Mexican Team Sets Up Second Camp on Everest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A U.S.-Mexican team trying to climb Mount
Everest has set up its second high-altitude camp on the world's
tallest peak, according to a message from the team Thursday.
   The camp was set up April 9 at 20,992 feet on the 29,028-foot
mountain.
   The team, led by Walter McConnel, 58, of Wharton, N.J., is
following the southeast ridge in its climb.
