<HEAD>Central Park Jogger Gang-Raped</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An investment banker on her regular jog through
Central Park was raped and beaten unconscious by a teen-age gang
that attacked two other people in a late-night crime spree, police
said Thursday.
   The 30-year-old victim was in critical condition at Metropolitan
Hospital after the Wednesday night assault, said Chief of
Detectives Robert Colangelo.
   Two pedestrians found the victim, wearing only a bra and bound
and gagged with a sweatshirt, about 1:30 a.m. She had a fractured
skull and her body temperature was 80 degrees when she was
discovered.
   Colangelo said evidence indicated the woman fought desperately
against at least a dozen assailants.
   Three suspects were in custody. Two others had been arrested and
released before the unconscious woman was discovered, Colangelo
said. Police were searching for up to seven additional suspects,
all ages 13 to 15.
   As many as 20 youths came to the park about 10 p.m. from upper
Manhattan, said Deputy Commissioner Alice McGillion.
   The gang used a pipe to assault and rob a 40-year-old man
carrying his groceries home through the park, Colangelo said.
   Police believe the jogger was attacked next, with several gang
members then assaulting another woman, Colangelo said. The five
suspects were arrested in the attack on the man, said McGillion.
