<HEAD>Child Killed, 25 Hurt in Shantytown Demolition</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Witnesses said a child was killed and
at least 25 people were injured Thursday, when police and municipal
workers bulldozed a shantytown in an upper-class neighborhood of
the capital.
   Susan Davis, a program officer with the Ford Foundation, said
she saw the body of a young girl and saw several injured men after
the demolition in the Gulshan district.
