said at least 10 people were treated for injuries. Ms. Davis said
at least 15 injured people did not go to the hospital.
   Police said about 2,000 people were evicted but denied using
force or causing casualties. Muncipal officials were not available
for comment.
   Ms. Davis said she was shown empty tear gas canisters, which
residents said were fired by police before demolition began.
   ``I saw the poor people gathering their belongings after the
evictions,'' she said. ``It was terrible. I was shocked to see the
rampage.''
