<TEXT>
   Stock prices kept climbing Wednesday, getting a little more
mileage out of a rally that has carried the market to its highest
levels since the crash of 1987. The Dow Jones industrials average
rose 7.51 to 2,386.91, bringing its gain over the past four
sessions to 90.91 points.
   The dollar bounced back, boosted by higher oil prices.
   Bond prices dipped slightly in quiet trading.
   Prices for corn and soybeans to be harvested this fall fell
sharply; wheat futures rose; livestock and meat futures prices
tumbled; and precious metals were slightly lower.
