<HEAD>Ford Recalls 47,000 Cars Made for California Sale</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: CORRECTS to 1985, sted 1885 in 2nd graf; no pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. is recalling about 47,000
Ford and Mercury cars made for sale in California, citing an
emissions control problem.
   The company said the recall involved 1985-86 Ford Mustang,
Thunderbird and LTD, and Mercury Capri, Cougar and Marquis cars
equipped with 3.8-liter, V-6 engines and automatic transmissions.
   Testing in California showed that emissions of some gases were
too high, Ford said in a Wednesday statement. Dealers will replace
an exhaust system part free of charge.
