<TEXT>
   Two Baby Bell phone companies reported higher first-quarter
earnings Thursday, up 6 percent at Bell Atlantic Corp. and 3.8
percent at U S West Inc.
   Philadelphia-based Bell Atlantic said earnings rose to $348.8
million, or $1.77 a share, from $329.1 million, or $1.66 a share, a
