million, or $1.30 a share, during first-quarter 1988. Sales rose to
$2.39 billion for the quarter, compared to $2.19 billion during
that period last year.
   U S West attributed mainly to gains by the telephone company's
commercial real estate subsidiary, BetaWest Properties. The
quarter's figures reflect its sale of City Financial Tower in
Honolulu. Terms were not disclosed.
