<HEAD>Production Up This Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
255,151 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
247,819, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 247,282 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 161,119 cars this week,
compared with 160,476 a week ago and 160,037 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 94,032,
compared with last week's 87,343 and last year's 87,245.
   Canadian automakers were to build 20,826 cars this week, down
from 21,939 a week ago and from last year's 26,687.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,347,
compared with 18,919 a week ago and 21,060 in the same week last
year.
</TEXT>
