<HEAD>Aerospace Company's Chairman to Resign</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Northrop Corp.'s chairman and chief
executive, Thomas V. Jones, announced Thursday he will retire as
chief executive of the company that makes the B-2 stealth bomber
and other high-tech military hardware.
