executive by Kent Kresa, 51, who has been president and chief
operating officer since 1987, the company said.
   Jones, who joined Northrop in 1953, will retain the chairman's
post.
   Kresa was hired by Northrop in 1975 and has headed the aircraft
group, among other executive posts at the company.
   The succession was planned, the company said.
