<FILEID>AP-NR-04-20-89 2139EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>d f BC-PetroleumReview     04-20 0775</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Petroleum Review,0484</SECOND>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Total crude runs to stills averaged 13,040,000
barrels daily during the week ended Friday, April 14, the American
Petroleum Institute reported Thursday. This compared with
12,998,000 barrels daily in the previous week and 13,177,000
barrels daily a year ago.
   Crude runs east of California averaged 10,468,000 barrels daily
compared with 10,551,000 the previous week and 10,531,000 a year
ago.
   Motor gasoline production for the latest week amounted to
6,692,000 barrels a day, compared with 6,644,000 barrels a day in
the previous week and 6,956,000 a day a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline production was 5,572,000 a day
compared with 5,565,000 a day last week and 5,764,000 a day a year
ago.
   Motor gasoline stocks at the end of the latest week were
225,426,000 barrels, versus 227,535,000 a week earlier and
229,224,000 a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline stocks totaled 199,226,000
barrels compared with 201,441,000 in the previous week and
200,512,000 barrels last year.
   Daily average gross crude oil and lease condensate production
for the week ended Friday was 7,848,000 barrels compared with
8,236,000 last year.
   Crude oil stocks totaled 320,203,000 barrels at the close of
last week, against 325,918,000 a week previous and 352,409,000 a
year ago.
   East of California crude stocks amounted to 250,416,000 barrels,
compared with 251,575,000 a week earlier.
   Daily imports east of California for the week ended Friday were
crude oil, 5,633,000 barrels, residual fuel oil, 610,000,
distillate fuel oil, 348,O00, and others 1,219,000, a total of
7,810,000 barrels.
   California imports were: crude oil 131,000 barrels, and products
42,000, a total of 173,000 barrels, for a grand total of 7,983,000.
   For the four weeks, daily imports east of California were crude
oil 4,947,000 barrels, residual fuel oil 307,000, distillate fuel
oil 214,000, and others 594,000, for a total of 6,062,000 barrels.
   For the four weeks, California daily imports averaged for crude
oil 163,000 barrels, products 69,000, a total of 232,000 barrels,
for a grand total of 6,294,000.
