<HEAD>Phillips, Amerada Hess Report Higher Earnings; Amoco Profit Down</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Amoco Corp. said Thursday its first-quarter profit fell about 2
percent due to a $57 million special charge stemming from a
restructuring of its exploration and production operations.
   Phillips Petroleum Co., meanwhile, posted a 46 percent gain in
net earnings and Amerada Hess Corp.'s first-quarter profit more
than doubled, the companies said.
