$190 million, or 78 cents a share, compared with $130 million, or
55 cents a share, in the 1988 quarter.
   The company's revenue totaled $3.1 billion, up from $2.9 billion
in the year-earlier period.
   New York-based Amerada Hess posted a profit of $220 million, or
$2.70 a share, compared with net income of $65.6 million, or 80
cents a share, for the first quarter of 1988.
   Revenue came to $1.5 billion, up from $1.26 billion a year
earlier.
