<HEAD>Georgia-Pacific Reports Sharp Rise In Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Georgia-Pacific Corp. reported Thursday that its
first-quarter profit rose 45 percent, boosted by strong performance
in its pulp and paper operations.
   The Atlanta-based wood and paper products company said its
first-quarter profit was $154 million, or $1.65 a share, up from
$106 million, or $1.02 a share, in the same quarter of 1988.
   Revenue for the quarter totaled $2.4 billion, up from $2.1
billion in the year-earlier period.
