<FIRST>r f AM-ColemanBuyout 1stLd-Writethru f0227 04-20 0220</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Coleman Buyout, 1st Ld-Writethru, f0227,0223</SECOND>
<HEAD>Coleman Family To Tender To Perelman</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: CORRECTS spelling of ``Perelman'' throughout.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WICHITA, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The founding family of Coleman Co. said
Thursday it will tender its stake to takeover specialist Ronald O.
Perelman, who has made a $545 million bid for the outdoor products
company.
   Coleman Chairman and Chief Executive Sheldon C. Coleman,
grandson of the company's founder, said he and other family members
and the trusts they control would tender their approximately
1,880,000 shares to Lantern Acquisition Corp., a wholly owned
subsidiary of Perelman's MacAndrews &amp; Forbes Holdings Inc.
   ``We believe that the way the MacAndrews &amp; Forbes offer was
structured virtually assures its success regardless of our
actions,'' Sheldon C. Coleman said. ``At this point, the Coleman
family believes it is in the best interests of our company to
support the new owners and work toward building an exciting future
for the people of Coleman.''
   A definitive merger agreement was announced last month under
which Perelman would acquire Coleman for $74 a share in cash,
topping a family offer to take the company private for $68 per
share in cash and stock.
   Coleman is the world's largest manufacturer of outdoor
recreation products including its famous lanterns, cookstoves and
coolers. It also has a home heating and air conditioning division.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
